personalInfo.splInterest: Fishing, hunting, spending time with family and friends

tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T10 at the Sebring, FL Q-School in January, but did not make any starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica.

2014: Had two top-25s and six cuts made in 8 starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica, where he finished the season ranked 107th on the Order of Merit... Best finish was T22 at the Guatemala Stella Artois Open in March.

tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Additional Qualifying Tournament Finisher or Finished 76-100 on 2014 Web.com Tour Money List
tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Played eight Latinoamérica events, making six cuts. Best finish came at the Stella Artois Open (T22), followed by T23, T25 and T27 efforts...Made his first PGA TOUR appearance, at the HP Byron Nelson Championship (missed the cut)...Lone Web.com Tour start was in Midland, Texas, where he finished T51...Finished 148th at Web.com Tour Q-School Finals.

2013: His first Web.com Tour start resulted in a missed cut at the Mylan Classic near Pittsburgh, Pa.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Two-time Palmer Cup team member (2011 and 2013), two-time Division II Jack Nicklaus Award Winner as Player of the Year (2011 and 2013). Recorded 20 collegiate wins in Abilene Christian career. Four-time Lone Star Conference Player of the Year...Won the 2010 Southern Amateur...Was high school state champion four years and 2009 Texas-Oklahoma state champion.
tourBios.personal: Attended Arkansas Baptist High School in Little Rock...Favorite golf memory is draining a 70-foot eagle putt on No. 17 at Shoal Creek that helped clinch the victory at the 2010 Southern Amateur...If he weren't playing golf he would be a professional bass fisherman...Biggest thrill in golf is winning 20 collegiate tournaments...Best concert attended was Jason Aldean and Florida Georgia Line in Dallas...Not many people know that he had a fishing show on ESPN called "The Casting Crew."...Would like to trade places with his yellow labrador Champ for a day...Entrance song on the first tee would be Aaron Watson's "3rd Gear & 17."...Has wanted to play professional golf since he was 10...Twitter handle is @acugolfer.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T51st in 2014 at the WNB Golf Classic.
